----- stdout -----
List internal crate use statements from a module

Usage: crawk use [OPTIONS] <MODULE_PATH>

Arguments:
  <MODULE_PATH>  Module path to analyze (e.g., "utils" or "foo::bar::baz")

Options:
  -t, --include-tests  Include test modules in the analysis
  -p, --path <PATH>    Path to the crate root directory (defaults to current directory)
  -v, --verbose        Show verbose output including crate root, module path, and analysis info
  -e, --expand         Expand grouped imports into individual paths (e.g., a::b::{x, y} -> a::b::x, a::b::y)
  -d, --depth <DEPTH>  Limit module depth from crate root (e.g., --depth 1 shows crate::x, --depth 2 shows crate::x::y)
  -h, --help           Print help

